PURPOSE: The aim of this study was to evaluate the 6-year effectiveness of 
maxillary and mandibular full-arch immediately loaded prostheses fabricated 
using an intraoral welding technique.
METHODS: All patients received the same day of surgery a fixed, full-arch 
prosthesis supported by an intraorally welded titanium framework created 
directly in the patient's mouth using a titanium bar. Life table analysis of 
implant survival, complications, and any other adverse events were recorded at 
