in the mandible (n = 87). Fracturing of the composite resin superstructure was 
the most common adverse event.
CONCLUSIONS: After a 6-year follow-up period, the intraoral welding technique 
proved to be a predictable technique for successfully rehabilitating the fully 
edentulous patient with a fixed and immediate prosthesis.

